# G1 — Frontmatter audit + `tier`/`kind` fields + CONVENTIONS.md

**Workstream:** harness-rigorization
**Wave:** 1 (no dependencies)
**Effort:** 2 pts
**Type:** Extend

## Goal

Standardize the frontmatter contract across all 26 skills. Codify the rigidity classification (`tier`) and priority class (`kind`). Write `.claude/skills/CONVENTIONS.md` so future contributors know the shape.

This is the foundation — every later sub-plan references the conventions written here.

## Dependencies

None. Lands first.

## Key Decisions (already made)

- Frontmatter required fields: `name`, `description`, `user-invocable`, `tier`. `kind` required when `tier != util`.
- `tier` enum: `rigid | flexible | util`.
- `kind` enum: `process | implementation | verification`.
- `description` MUST be a trigger ("Use when…"), never a workflow summary. This is enforced in CONVENTIONS.md and validated in `/harness-health`.
- `name` MUST match the skill folder name. The current `build-plan/SKILL.md` declares `name: build` — that gets fixed here.

